{"type":"message","id":"fef8b6a3","parentId":"6e3c677e","timestamp":"2026-04-10T01:25:15.987Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to sync the current state to the backup repo. The strategy is:\n1. Copy files from local ~/.openclaw to the clone, respecting .gitignore\n2. But wait - openclaw.json is in .gitignore, which means credentials are excluded. Good.\n3. Actually, I need to think about what's worth backing up. The local directories that matter:\n   - agents/ (configs, sessions)\n   - workspace/ (workspace files)\n   - workspace-selector/\n   - workspace-main/\n   - skills/ (custom skills in workspace)\n   - cron/jobs.json\n   - identity/\n   - openviking/ (data)\n   - openclaw.json (config, but excluded from gitignore - wait, it IS in .gitignore)\n\nWait, openclaw.json is in .gitignore. But we still want to back it up, just without tokens. \n\nI should check the previous approach - it looks like the backup repo was directly copying from ~/.openclaw, and there's already a scheduled workflow for daily backups. Let me verify if that workflow still exists in the repo.\n\nActually, I'm realizing the right approach here is to push directly from the local machine to the backup repo. I'll create the GitHub Actions workflow file to handle the backup process, then sync the current state by staging and committing changes."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dmmj9l5fpc2r_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mkdir -p /tmp/openclaw-backup-clone/.github/workflows"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775784305825,"responseId":"062784728973d2a1e30bca28713453be"}}
