{"type":"message","id":"dd623e92","parentId":"d82237d1","timestamp":"2026-04-10T01:27:31.081Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so the OpenClaw system seems to be the OpenClaw-Admin project. The cron commands I was trying aren't working because the gateway is busy.\n\nLet me think about a different approach. The backup was done via a script that:\n1. Zips up the important files\n2. Uses gh to push to the openclaw-backup repo\n\nLooking at the backup repo structure, it has files synced from the local machine to the repo. The last backup was 2026-04-09.\n\nFor a daily automated backup, I need to create a cron job that:\n1. Uses rsync or git to sync the local files to the cloned repo directory\n\n\n2. Commits and pushes changes\n\nI should write a backup script and schedule it with a traditional cron job since the OpenClaw cron doesn't seem to be working. I'll create the script, commit it to the backup repo so it's version controlled, then set up a cron entry to run it daily.\n\nBut I realize the actual workflow would be: the script pulls from GitHub, rsyncs the local OpenClaw files to the clone, then commits and pushes. This keeps the GitHub repo as the source of truth while ensuring local changes get backed up. Since the user wants to restore to a new machine, having everything in GitHub makes sense.\n\nFor the daily backup to work, I need to figure out how to set up the cron job properly.\n\nI'm realizing the core issue: the backup script needs to exist on the machine to run daily, but I don't know where it was originally stored. The best approach is to create the backup script in the workspace, add it to the backup repo, then set up a cron job to execute it every day. The script will sync the OpenClaw directories to the cloned repo and push the changes to GitHub."},{"type":"text","text":"Gateway 有点卡住了，换个方式——直接写备份脚本 + 传统 cron。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wk1wd3gv5tqf_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace/skills/openclaw-backup/backup.sh","content":"#!/bin/bash\n# OpenClaw Daily Backup Script\n# Syncs local OpenClaw state to GitHub backup repo\n\nBACKUP_REPO=\"/tmp/openclaw-backup-clone\"\nOPENCLAW_DIR=\"$HOME/.openclaw\"\nGIT_REF=\"main\"\n\nset -e\n\necho \"[$(date)] Starting OpenClaw backup...\"\n\n# Sync from GitHub first (in case of changes from other machines)\ncd \"$BACKUP_REPO\"\ngit checkout \"$GIT_REF\" 2>/dev/null || git clone https://github.com/59330857/openclaw-backup.git \"$BACKUP_REPO\"\ngit pull origin \"$GIT_REF\" --quiet\n\n# Sync key directories\nrsync -a --delete \\\n  \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/agents/\" \\\n  \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/workspace/\" \\\n  \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/workspace-main/\" \\\n  \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/workspace-selector/\" \\\n  \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/agents/tts/\" \\\n  \"$BACKUP_REPO/\"\n\n# Also backup skills (workspace-skills only, not the global ones)\nrsync -a --delete \\\n  \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/workspace/skills/\" \\\n  \"$BACKUP_REPO/\"\n\n# Sync openviking config (not the full db, just config)\nrsync -a --delete \\\n  \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/openviking/\" \\\n  \"$BACKUP_REPO/\"\n\n# Commit and push if there are changes\ncd \"$BACKUP_REPO\"\nif git diff --quiet && git diff --cached --quiet; then\n  echo \"[$(date)] No changes, skipping commit\"\nelse\n  git add -A\n  git commit -m \"Full backup $(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M')\"\n  git push origin \"$GIT_REF\"\n  echo \"[$(date)] Backup pushed to GitHub\"\nfi\n"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775784427920,"responseId":"062784ec914e0f1fa65c64f0084c4388"}}
