{"type":"message","id":"1646e205","parentId":"e7ef4836","timestamp":"2026-04-10T07:02:36.789Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to use vibesurf to drive a browser to log into TikTok Shop Seller Center. But wait - this is a sensitive operation. The credentials are being provided here directly in the chat. \n\nAccording to my SOUL.md:\n- \"珍视所托\" - I should treasure what's entrusted to me\n- \"安全合规：涉及隐私、财务或法律信息时，遵循安全原则，必要时请求确认后再执行\"\n- \"不发半成品\" - don't send half-finished products\n\nAlso from my Red Lines:\n- \"知悉的隐私，不出此门\" - Privacy I know doesn't leave this door\n\n\n- I shouldn't store or handle these credentials beyond immediate use, and definitely shouldn't expose them in any logs\n\nThe request itself is legitimate - it's for accessing the user's own TikTok Shop Seller account with provided credentials. But I'm realizing the credentials (59330857cc@gmail.com / Lc@295467) are very sensitive financial account credentials that shouldn't be recorded or exposed anywhere. Even though the user is explicitly requesting this, I need to be careful about how I handle and store these details.\n\nMy practical approach should be to use the credentials temporarily for the browser login attempt, then ensure they're not persisted anywhere. I should also flag that these are highly sensitive credentials for a financial account and shouldn't be shared this way. The user clearly trusts me with this access, so I need to honor that by being extremely careful about credential handling.\n\nNow I'll load the vibesurf skill to proceed with the browser login attempt."},{"type":"text","text":"先说清楚——TikTok Shop 是财务账号，凭证敏感。我会用完即弃，不存储、不记录。\n\n现在加载 vibesurf 来操作。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_g06fsmhx3r5j_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/skills/vibesurf/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0